description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated individual to lead our team of MDT Co-ordinators and Cancer Audit Facilitators within the Cancer Services Cluster. This dynamic team provides a critical role in cancer patient pathways supporting clinical staff across the cancer MDTs. Within the role you will also work with senior management teams to lead on the development of our MDT and audit service across Cancer ensuring that the team development is in line with the Trust and national cancer agendas to ensure optimum care for patients. The role also includes close working with the clinical and CNS teams to provide high quality data services as well as working with the teams to make submissions on behalf of the MDT and the Trust for national, regional and local use. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role also will provide central leadership of the Cancer MDT and Audit team in the transition of services post the MY CARE launch in October 2020, leading change and innovation across Cancer Services. The role also involves being a central point of contact for managing and maintaining local and national cancer registries using MY CARE, InfoFlex and Dendrite cancer data systems, providing advice to IM&amp;T and senior management teams on the dataset requirements and specifications required. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will need to be organised with the ability to multi-task and prioritise their workload. Experience in HR management would be beneficial however training and guidance will be given. You should have a flexible approach to work and must have the ability to lead complex teams through processes of change.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information about this post and the role please contact Amy Fullick, Peer Review and Governance Lead, Cancer Services on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;amy.fullick@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness,&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
